shapes."},"1006":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is intended for use inside chart components."},"1007":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#props","content":"The `Tooltip` component accepts the following props:"},"1008":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-14","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Default:** When `formatValue` is not provided, the tooltip uses a formatter that reads the data point’s `y` property (same as the chart's default Y accessor), converts it to a string, and returns an empty string for null. This is correct for the default `DataPoint` shape (`{ x, y }`)."},"1009":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-15","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Custom:** Pass `formatValue` to control display. The function receives the datum and returns a string. Use it to both extract and format (e.g. currency, percentage, custom units). For custom data point shapes (generic `TooltipProps<YourDatum>`), you must pass `formatValue` because the default only reads `y`."},"1010":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-16","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#single-series","content":"Basic tooltip with a single series and default formatting."},"1011":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-17","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#multiple-series","content":"Tooltip with multiple series; all series at the same X position are shown together."},"1012":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-18","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#arrow","content":"Use the `showArrow` prop to set whether the tooltip arrow is visible or not."},"1013":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"page","content":"TooltipDismissStrip","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip"},"1014":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","content":"Internal visx XYChart helper that closes the tooltip when the pointer enters a leading-edge strip over scroll-synced axis chrome"},"1015":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"Internal Component"},"1016":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#props","content":"Props"},"1017":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#examples","content":"Examples"},"1018":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#basic","content":"Basic"},"1019":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is designed for use within chart components."},"1020":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#props","content":"The `TooltipDismissStrip` component accepts the following props:"},"1021":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#basic","content":"Tooltip provider, relative container, optional controls to open the visx tooltip and the dismiss strip on the leading edge."},"1022":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"page","content":"useNormalizedSeries","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series"},"1023":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","content":"A hook that guarantees every series config has a stable, unique id by filling in missing ones with a component-scoped prefix from useId."},"1024":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1025":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#examples","content":"Examples"},"1026":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#mixed-ids","content":"Mixed ids"},"1027":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"Returns your series list with an `id` guaranteed on every item. Ids you provided are kept as-is; missing ones are filled in for you, stay stable across renders, and won't collide when multiple charts share the page."},"1028":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#mixed-ids","content":"The first item provides an explicit `id` and is preserved as-is; the remaining two have no `id` and are filled with stable generated ones (`<prefix>-1`, `<prefix>-2`)."},"1029":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"page","content":"useScrollableXYChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart"},"1030":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","content":"A hook for scrollable visx XY charts that measures the rendered axes and returns margins, content-sized width and height, scroll offsets, and a vertical-labels flag, so the chart sizes itself to whatever it actually contains."},"1031":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1032":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1033":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Auto layout"},"1034":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Inputs.** Wire `parentRef` to the scroll container and `xAxisRef` / `yAxisRef` to the axis groups. Optionally pass `xLabelsOrientation` (`'auto'` | `'horizontal'` | `'vertical'`, default `'auto'`) to force the category-label layout; `'auto'` rotates labels vertical when the visible width can't fit the horizontal-tick footprint plus the Y-axis width."},"1035":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Outputs.** The hook returns `margin`, `chartWidth`, `chartHeight`, `xLabelsVertical`, `scrollLeft` / `scrollTop`, and `yAxisRect` for the chart to consume. Width and height are sized to whichever is larger — the visible slot or the room the rendered labels need — so the chart grows past the viewport and the parent scrolls when labels demand more space."},"1036":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Behavior.** Measurement runs through `useParentSize`, a `MutationObserver`, and a `ResizeObserver` on the wired nodes. All axis measurements are batched in one `requestAnimationFrame` and bail out when the result hasn't changed, so a burst of observer fires costs at most one reflow and one render per frame."},"1037":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Hook wired to a scrolling parent; scroll or resize to watch the returned values update."},"1038":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"page","content":"useChartColor","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color"},"1039":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","content":"A hook for assigning deterministic, index-based colors to chart series using design token CSS variables. Safe under React concurrent rendering."},"1040":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1041":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#props","content":"Props"},"1042":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#examples","content":"Examples"},"1043":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-